 resistance and the ethical tensions and contradictions that arise, as well as with the dispossession and suffocation of people living under occupation and their ordinary lives in such times. Whether this story leaves readers discomforted, angry, or empowered, they will certainly emerge with a deeper understanding of the Palestinian predicament.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Israel & Palestine.2bisacsh  aGender.  aIslamic Jihad.  aIsrael.  aMemory.  aMigration.  aMilitary Occupation.  aOral History.  aPalestine.  aResistance.  aSuicide bombing.1 aHermez, Sami, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSawalha, Sireen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079133440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363706140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503637061423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503637061/original  a978-3-11-079133-4  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles